Part 1: Data sources

There are three data sources used for the analysis of the COBRA-ENV2 study: Bacteria Counts, Fungi Counts, and Meta Data.

The Bacteria Counts and Fungi Counts datasets contain sequencing counts and total counts for 967 bacterial taxa (genus level or higher) and 3,709 fungal taxa (species level or higher), respectively, across 62 individual samples. The Meta Data dataset contains individual-level covariates, including clinical status (case = asthmatic; control = healthy). All three data sources are stored in the COBRA-ENV2.RData file.

load("COBRA-ENV2.RData")

Part 2: Proportion data and filters

The first step is transform the sequence counts to proportion data, dividing by the total number of sequence counts per sample, and then filtering the bacterial and fungal taxa, according to the following criteria:

  • Presence: the taxon is present in at least 5% of the samples, where it registers a value greater than zero;
  • Abundance: the proportion data for the taxon exceed 1% at least in one sample.
dat.bact.mod<-dat.clin %>% 
  left_join(dat.bact %>% 
              column_to_rownames("Sample") %>% 
              transmute(across(where(is.numeric),~.x/TotalCount)) %>% 
              select(-TotalCount) %>% 
              dplyr::select(where(~is.numeric(.x) & mean(.x>0)>=0.05 & max(.x)>=0.01)) %>% 
              rownames_to_column("Sample"),join_by(Sample))

dat.fung.mod<-dat.clin %>% 
  left_join(dat.fung %>% 
              column_to_rownames("Sample") %>% 
              transmute(across(where(is.numeric),~.x/TotalCount)) %>% 
              select(-TotalCount) %>% 
              dplyr::select(where(~is.numeric(.x) & mean(.x>0)>=0.05 & max(.x)>=0.01)) %>% 
              rownames_to_column("Sample"),join_by(Sample))

# Taxa for analysis

taxa.bact<-colnames(dat.bact.mod)[(dim(dat.clin)[2]+1):(dim(dat.bact.mod)[2])]
taxa.fung<-colnames(dat.fung.mod)[(dim(dat.clin)[2]+1):(dim(dat.fung.mod)[2])]

After this step, 101 bacteria genus and 139 fungi species remain for the next part.

dat.bact.div<-dat.bact %>% column_to_rownames("Sample") %>% dplyr::select(all_of(taxa.bact))

# Chao1

bact.div.chao1<-specnumber(dat.bact.div) %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  set_names("Chao1") %>% 
  rownames_to_column("Sample")

# Shannon

bact.div.shannon<-diversity(dat.bact.div,index="shannon") %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  set_names("Shannon") %>% 
  rownames_to_column("Sample")

# Simpson

bact.div.simpson<-diversity(dat.bact.div,index="simpson") %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  set_names("Simpson") %>% 
  rownames_to_column("Sample")

# Diversity dataframe and Pielou index computation

dat.bact.div<-bact.div.shannon %>% 
  left_join(bact.div.simpson) %>% 
  left_join(bact.div.chao1) %>% 
  mutate(Pielou=Shannon/log(Chao1)) %>% 
  left_join(dat.clin[,c(1,4)],join_by(Sample)) %>% 
  mutate(Asthma=factor(Asthma,levels=c("Yes","No")))

Part 4: DAA: models for asthma significance

To detect taxa in which asthma represents a statistically significant influence, we used a beta regression model that includes a zero inflation component only if the percentage of zeros in the proportions of each taxon exceeds 80% of the samples. In addition, two specifications are used for the model covariates:

  1. Fixed effects: model with fixed effects for all covariates (individual and environmental) in both abundance and presence (if necessary).
  2. Mixed effects: model with fixed effects for individual covariates, and a random intercept grouped by the geographical cluster, both in abundance and presence parts (if necessary).

DAA (bacteria)

# Covariates for the 3 specifications

covar0<-c("Asthma")
covar1<-c("Asthma","Sex","AgeGroup","ForestationRate","Zone","Humidity","Air_Quality","PollenGroup","Mold")
covar2<-c("Asthma","Sex","AgeGroup","Mold")

Crude model (bacteria)

# Cycle 0: crude model

models.crude<-list()
taxa.crude<-c()

for(type in taxa.bact)
{
  #type="01D2Z36"
  y<-pull(dat.bact.mod,type)
  if(mean(y>0)<=0.8)
  {
    tabmod<-dat.bact.mod %>% 
      dplyr::select(Sample,contains(type),all_of(covar0))
    form<-reformulate(c("1",covar0),as.name(type))
    form1<-formula(paste(" ",paste(covar0,collapse=" + "),sep=" ~ "))
    mod<-try(glmmTMB(form,data=tabmod,family=beta_family(link="logit"),ziformula = form1),silent=T)
    flag<-((!is.nan(coef(summary(mod))$cond["AsthmaYes",4]) & coef(summary(mod))$cond["AsthmaYes",4]<0.05) | 
             (!is.nan(coef(summary(mod))$zi["AsthmaYes",4]) & coef(summary(mod))$zi["AsthmaYes",4]<0.05))
  }
  else
  {
    tabmod<-dat.bact.mod %>% 
      dplyr::select(Sample,contains(type),all_of(covar0)) %>% 
      mutate(across(contains(type),~ifelse(.x==0,1e-9,.x)))
    form<-reformulate(c("1",covar0),as.name(type))
    mod<-try(glmmTMB(form,data=tabmod,family=beta_family(link="logit")),silent=T)
    flag<-(!is.nan(coef(summary(mod))$cond["AsthmaYes",4]) & coef(summary(mod))$cond["AsthmaYes",4]<0.05)
  }
  models.crude[[type]]<-mod
  if(flag) taxa.crude<-c(taxa.crude,type)
}

With this model 17 significant bacterial taxa.

Mixed effects model (bacteria)

# Cycle 2: mixed effects model

models.clust<-list()
taxa.clust<-c()

for(type in taxa.bact)
{
  #type="Clostridiisalibacter"
  y<-pull(dat.bact.mod,type)
  if(mean(y>0)<=0.8)
  {
    tabmod<-dat.bact.mod %>% 
      dplyr::select(Clust,contains(type),all_of(covar2))
    form<-reformulate(c("(1|Clust)",covar2),as.name(type))
    form1<-formula(paste(" ",paste(c("(1|Clust)",covar2),collapse=" + "),sep=" ~ "))
    mod<-try(glmmTMB(form,data=tabmod,family=beta_family(link="logit"),ziformula = form1))
    flag<-((!is.nan(coef(summary(mod))$cond["AsthmaYes",4]) & coef(summary(mod))$cond["AsthmaYes",4]<0.05) | 
             (!is.nan(coef(summary(mod))$zi["AsthmaYes",4]) & coef(summary(mod))$zi["AsthmaYes",4]<0.05))
  }
  else
  {
    tabmod<-dat.bact.mod %>% 
      dplyr::select(Clust,contains(type),all_of(covar2)) %>% 
      mutate(across(contains(type),~ifelse(.x==0,1e-9,.x)))
    form<-reformulate(c("(1|Clust)",covar2),as.name(type))
    mod<-try(glmmTMB(form,data=tabmod,family=beta_family(link="logit")))
    flag<-(!is.nan(coef(summary(mod))$cond["AsthmaYes",4]) & coef(summary(mod))$cond["AsthmaYes",4]<0.05)
  }
  models.clust[[type]]<-mod
  if(flag) taxa.clust<-c(taxa.clust,type)
}

With this model 17 significant bacterial taxa.

We construct now table of results:

btable<-sort(unique(c(taxa.fixed,taxa.clust)))
btaxasign <- as.data.frame(
  matrix(NA, nrow = length(btable), ncol = 18)
)

rownames(btaxasign) <- btable

names(btaxasign) <- c(
  'PrevaP','PrevaC',
  'CrudeZI','CrudeZIp',
  'FixedZI','FixedZIp',
  'REZI','REZIp',
  'MP','SDP','MC','SDC',
  'Crude','Crudep',
  'Fixed','Fixedp',
  'RE','REp'
)

for (i in seq_along(btable)) {
  
  nom <- btable[i]
  x <- dat.bact[[nom]]
  
  ## --- Prvalences
  btaxasign[i,'PrevaP'] <- round(100 * sum(x[1:42] != 0) / 42, 0)
  btaxasign[i,'PrevaC'] <- round(100 * sum(x[43:62] != 0) / 20, 0)
  
  ## --- Moyennes et SD (non-zros)
  btaxasign[i,'MP'] <- round(1000*mean(x[1:42][x[1:42] != 0]/dat.bact$TotalCount[1:42][x[1:42] != 0]),0)
  btaxasign[i,'SDP'] <- round(1000*sd(x[1:42][x[1:42] != 0]/dat.bact$TotalCount[1:42][x[1:42] != 0]),0)

  
  btaxasign[i,'MC'] <- round(1000*mean(x[43:62][x[43:62] != 0]/dat.bact$TotalCount[43:62][x[43:62] != 0]),0)
  btaxasign[i,'SDC'] <- round(1000*sd(x[43:62][x[43:62] != 0]/dat.bact$TotalCount[43:62][x[43:62] != 0]),0)

  ## --- Modle crude
  sm <- summary(models.crude[[nom]])
  
  ## Partie conditionnelle
  btaxasign[i,'Crude']  <- round(sm$coefficients$cond[2,1], 1)
  btaxasign[i,'Crudep'] <- sm$coefficients$cond[2,4]
  
  ## Partie ZI (si elle existe)
  btaxasign[i,'CrudeZI']  <- btaxasign[i, 'CrudeZI'] <- tryCatch({
    val <- sm$coefficients$zi[2,1]
    if (is.null(val)) NA else round(val, 1)
  }, error = function(e) NA)
  btaxasign[i,'CrudeZIp'] <- btaxasign[i, 'CrudeZIp'] <- tryCatch({
    val <- sm$coefficients$zi[2,4]
    if (is.null(val)) NA else val
  }, error = function(e) NA)
  

  ## --- Modle Fixed
  sm <- summary(models.fixed[[nom]])
  
  ## Partie conditionnelle
  btaxasign[i,'Fixed']  <- round(sm$coefficients$cond[2,1], 1)
  btaxasign[i,'Fixedp'] <- sm$coefficients$cond[2,4]
  
  ## Partie ZI (si elle existe)
  btaxasign[i,'FixedZI']  <- btaxasign[i, 'FixedZI'] <- tryCatch({
    val <- sm$coefficients$zi[2,1]
    if (is.null(val)) NA else round(val, 1)
  }, error = function(e) NA)
  btaxasign[i,'FixedZIp'] <- tryCatch({
    val <- sm$coefficients$zi[2,4]
    if (is.null(val)) NA else val
  }, error = function(e) NA)
  
  ## --- Modle RE
  sm <- summary(models.clust[[nom]])
  
  ## Partie conditionnelle
  btaxasign[i,'RE']  <- round(sm$coefficients$cond[2,1], 1)
  btaxasign[i,'REp'] <- sm$coefficients$cond[2,4]
  
  ## Partie ZI (si elle existe)
  btaxasign[i,'REZI']  <- btaxasign[i, 'REZI'] <- tryCatch({
    val <- sm$coefficients$zi[2,1]
    if (is.null(val)) NA else round(val, 1)
  }, error = function(e) NA)
  btaxasign[i,'REZIp'] <- btaxasign[i, 'REZIp'] <- tryCatch({
    val <- sm$coefficients$zi[2,4]
    if (is.null(val)) NA else val
  }, error = function(e) NA)
  
  
  }

p_to_code <- function(p) {
  ifelse(
    is.na(p), NA,
    ifelse(p < 0.005, 3,
           ifelse(p < 0.01, 2,
                  ifelse(p < 0.05, 1, 0)))
  )
}

pcols <- grep("p$", colnames(btaxasign), value = TRUE)

btaxasign[pcols] <- lapply(btaxasign[pcols], p_to_code)

    form<-reformulate(c("1",covar1),as.name(type))

    mod<-try(glmmTMB(form,data=tabmod,family=beta_family(link="logit"),ziformula = form1))
    flag<-((!is.nan(coef(summary(mod))$cond["AsthmaYes",4]) & coef(summary(mod))$cond["AsthmaYes",4]<0.05) | 
             (!is.nan(coef(summary(mod))$zi["AsthmaYes",4]) & coef(summary(mod))$zi["AsthmaYes",4]<0.05))
  }
  else
  {
    tabmod<-dat.fung.mod %>% 
      dplyr::select(Sample,contains(type),all_of(covar1)) %>% 
      mutate(across(contains(type),~ifelse(.x==0,1e-9,.x)))
    form<-reformulate(c("1",covar1),as.name(type))
    mod<-try(glmmTMB(form,data=tabmod,family=beta_family(link="logit")))
    flag<-(!is.nan(coef(summary(mod))$cond["AsthmaYes",4]) & coef(summary(mod))$cond["AsthmaYes",4]<0.05)
  }
  fmodels.fixed[[type]]<-mod
  if(flag) ftaxa.fixed<-c(ftaxa.fixed,type)
}

for (i in seq_along(ftable)) {
  
  nom <- ftable[i]
  x <- dat.fung[[nom]]
  
  ## --- Prvalences
  ftaxasign[i,'PrevaP'] <- round(100 * sum(x[1:42] != 0) / 42, 0)
  ftaxasign[i,'PrevaC'] <- round(100 * sum(x[43:62] != 0) / 20, 0)
  
  ## --- Moyennes et SD (non-zros)
  ftaxasign[i,'MP'] <- round(1000*mean(x[1:42][x[1:42] != 0]/dat.fung$TotalCount[1:42][x[1:42] != 0]),0)
  ftaxasign[i,'SDP'] <- round(1000*sd(x[1:42][x[1:42] != 0]/dat.fung$TotalCount[1:42][x[1:42] != 0]),0)

  ftaxasign[i,'MC'] <- round(1000*mean(x[43:62][x[43:62] != 0]/dat.fung$TotalCount[43:62][x[43:62] != 0]),0)
  ftaxasign[i,'SDC'] <- round(1000*sd(x[43:62][x[43:62] != 0]/dat.fung$TotalCount[43:62][x[43:62] != 0]),0)
  
  ## --- Modle crude
  sm <- summary(fmodels.crude[[nom]])
  
  ## Partie conditionnelle
  ftaxasign[i,'Crude']  <- round(sm$coefficients$cond[2,1], 1)
  ftaxasign[i,'Crudep'] <- sm$coefficients$cond[2,4]
  
  ## Partie ZI (si elle existe)
  ftaxasign[i,'CrudeZI']  <- ftaxasign[i, 'CrudeZI'] <- tryCatch({
    val <- sm$coefficients$zi[2,1]
    if (is.null(val)) NA else round(val, 1)
  }, error = function(e) NA)
  ftaxasign[i,'CrudeZIp'] <- ftaxasign[i, 'CrudeZIp'] <- tryCatch({
    val <- sm$coefficients$zi[2,4]
    if (is.null(val)) NA else val
  }, error = function(e) NA)
  

  ## --- Modle Fixed
  sm <- summary(fmodels.fixed[[nom]])
  
  ## Partie conditionnelle
  ftaxasign[i,'Fixed']  <- round(sm$coefficients$cond[2,1], 1)

  ## Partie ZI (si elle existe)

    val <- sm$coefficients$zi[2,1]

  }, error = function(e) NA)

  }, error = function(e) NA)

p_to_code <- function(p) {
  ifelse(
    is.na(p), NA,
    ifelse(p < 0.005, 3,
           ifelse(p < 0.01, 2,
                  ifelse(p < 0.05, 1, 0)))
  )
}

Based on the 33 bacterial and 67 fungal taxa, we will proceed to construct the inference networks using the PLNModels package.

Part 6: Networks for cases and controls

We create different networks for asthmatic patients and non-asthmatic controls. The covariates are zone (rural vs.urban), age group (more than 60 or below 60), and the humidity of the region.

# Installation of the version used (run just the first time!)

#require(devtools)
#install_version("PLNmodels", version = "1.2.0", repos = "http://cran.us.r-project.org")
library(PLNmodels)

# Offset matrix

offset.total<-do.call("cbind",replicate(ncol(dat.bact.net),rowSums(dat.bact.net),F)) %>% 
  cbind(do.call("cbind",replicate(ncol(dat.fung.net),rowSums(dat.fung.net),F)))
colnames(offset.total)<-c(colnames(dat.bact.net),colnames(dat.fung.net))

# Data for the network model

bact.prenet<-prepare_data(
  counts=dat.bact.net,
  covariates=dat.clin %>% column_to_rownames("Sample") %>% mutate(across(where(is.factor),~as.character(.x)))
)

fung.prenet<-prepare_data(
  counts=dat.fung.net,
  covariates=dat.clin %>% column_to_rownames("Sample") %>% mutate(across(where(is.factor),~as.character(.x)))
)

bactfung.prenet<-prepare_data(
  counts=cbind(bact.prenet$Abundance,fung.prenet$Abundance),
  covariates=dat.clin %>% column_to_rownames("Sample") %>% mutate(across(where(is.factor),~as.character(.x))),
  offset=offset.total
)

# Patients network model

patients.model<- ZIPLNnetwork(
  formula = Abundance ~ 0 + Zone + Humidity + AgeGroup + offset(log(Offset)) | 1 + Zone + Humidity + AgeGroup,
  data = bactfung.prenet,
  subset = Asthma=="Yes",
  control = ZIPLNnetwork_param(min_ratio = 0.3)
)

To create a better display of the networks obtained, we develop a function that differentiates between bacteria, fungi (and literature taxa in both cases).

filter.bib<-paste(c(taxa.selec.b,ftaxa.selec.b),collapse="|")
filter.bact<-paste(taxa.bact,collapse="|")

# Personalized function

plot.net.bf<-function(net)
{
  G<-graph_from_adjacency_matrix(net$latent_network(), mode = "undirected", weighted = TRUE, diag = FALSE)
  igraph::V(G)$label <- colnames(net$latent_network())
  G <- delete_vertices(G, which(degree(G) == 0))
  
  igraph::V(G)$label.cex <-ifelse(str_detect(igraph::V(G)$label,filter.bib),1,0.7)
  igraph::V(G)$size <- ifelse(str_detect(igraph::V(G)$label,filter.bib),12,4)
  igraph::V(G)$label.color <- "black"
  igraph::V(G)$shape <- ifelse(str_detect(igraph::V(G)$label,filter.bact),"square","circle")
  igraph::V(G)$color <- ifelse(str_detect(igraph::V(G)$label,filter.bact),"seagreen2","tomato2")
  igraph::V(G)$frame.color <- NA
  
  igraph::E(G)$color <- ifelse(igraph::E(G)$weight > 0, "#F8766D", "#00BFC4") # positivo rojo, negativo azul
  igraph::E(G)$width <- 15*abs(igraph::E(G)$weight)
  igraph::E(G)$weight<-abs(igraph::E(G)$weight)
  
  l <- qgraph.layout.fruchtermanreingold(get.edgelist(G,names=FALSE),vcount=vcount(G),
                                         area=80*(vcount(G)^2),repulse.rad=(vcount(G)^2.9))
  plot(G,layout=l)
  par(family = "serif")
  legend(x=.9,y=-0.9,legend=c("Bacteria","Fungi"),cex=0.9,pt.cex=2,
         col=c("seagreen2","tomato2"),pch=c(22,19),pt.bg=c("seagreen2","tomato2"),horiz=T)
  invisible(G)
}

plot.net.bf(patients.net)
